HEADWORD: Utriculus
<hw>U*tric"u*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a little
womb or matrix, a calycle.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A little sac,
or bag; a utricle; especially, a part of the membranous labyrinth of the
ear. See the Note under <er>Ear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utro-</ent>⟦br⟧
